15/11/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The Croatian Politics Society and the Zagreb Faculty of Political Science organised two days of talks on EU integration, ending on Saturday (13 November). 
Participants discussed legal and economic reforms, foreign and fiscal policies, educational aspects and the state of democracy in the country in the context of the country's bid to join the EU.
Meanwhile, strong winds paralysed traffic along Croatia's Adriatic coast on Sunday, triggering delays and power failures. 
Dozens of people were injured. 
Among the hardest hits areas was the resort town of Rijeka. 
(HRT, AFP - 14/11/04; Index.hr - 13/11/04; HINA - 12/11/04)
